    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nDeprecation warnings (and possibly other warnings) are cut off when the terminal size is small. Running `:messages` afterwards does not show the full message, it seems to be lost.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Resize terminal window to 70x25 (exact size does not matter)\n2. `nvim --clean`\n3. `:lua vim.lsp.set_log_level(\"WARN\")`\n4. optional: `:messages`\n\nThe output is cut off:\n\n    vim.lsp.set_log_level() is deprecated. Run \":checkhealth v\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOutput:\n\n    vim.lsp.set_log_level() is deprecated. Run \":checkhealth vim.deprecated\" for more information\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchlinux, up-to-date\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.26.1 +pgo +ime +graphemes +toplevel-tag +blur -assertions\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
